HEADWORD: Unpaganize
<hw>Un*pa"gan*ize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>paganize</ets>.]</ety> <def>To cause to cease to
be pagan; to divest of pagan character.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Cudworth.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
